<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="type material">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Type material.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Holotype</emphasis>
: JAPAN · ♂; Kagoshima-ken, Oshima-gun, Tokunoshima, Isen-cho, Kojima; 
<geoCoordinate degrees="27.74" direction="north" orientation="latitude" precision="555" value="27.74">27.74N</geoCoordinate>
, 
<geoCoordinate degrees="128.91" direction="east" orientation="longitude" precision="555" value="128.91">128.91E</geoCoordinate>
; alt. 160 m; 17 September 2013; D. Li and B. Wu leg.; XUX-2013-346 (matured 10 October 2013 at CBEE).
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Paratypes</emphasis>
: JAPAN · 2 ♂♂, 6 ♀♀; same data as for holotype; XUX-2013-339, 340, 342 to 345, 347, 348.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Males of 
<taxonomicName genus="H." lsidName="H. kojima" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="kojima">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">H. kojima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov. differ from those of 
<taxonomicName genus="H." lsidName="H. amamiensis" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="amamiensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">H. amamiensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName genus="H." lsidName="H. kanenoi" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="kanenoi">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">H. kanenoi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by a wide leaf-shaped conductor (
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 11" captionStartId="F11" captionText="Figure 11. Male and female genital anatomy of Heptathela kojima sp. nov. A, C 3339 (short for XUX- 2013 - 339) B, D 3340 E-G 3346 (holotype) H-K 3344 A, B vulva dorsal view C, D vulva ventral view E palp prolateral view F palp ventral view G palp retrolateral view H-K palp distal view. Scale bar: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.888.34494.figure11" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/354502" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" tableDoi="10.3897/zookeys.888.34494.figure11">Fig. 11I, J</figureCitation>
), and a less dentate dorsal extension of the tegular terminal apophysis (
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 11" captionStartId="F11" captionText="Figure 11. Male and female genital anatomy of Heptathela kojima sp. nov. A, C 3339 (short for XUX- 2013 - 339) B, D 3340 E-G 3346 (holotype) H-K 3344 A, B vulva dorsal view C, D vulva ventral view E palp prolateral view F palp ventral view G palp retrolateral view H-K palp distal view. Scale bar: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.888.34494.figure11" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/354502" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" tableDoi="10.3897/zookeys.888.34494.figure11">Fig. 11G, J, K</figureCitation>
), from those of 
<taxonomicName genus="H." lsidName="H. sumiyo" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="sumiyo">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">H. sumiyo</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov. by a shallow saddle-shaped in the prolateral view, and from those of 
<taxonomicName genus="H." lsidName="H. uken" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="uken">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">H. uken</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov. by embolus with two longer peaks (
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 11" captionStartId="F11" captionText="Figure 11. Male and female genital anatomy of Heptathela kojima sp. nov. A, C 3339 (short for XUX- 2013 - 339) B, D 3340 E-G 3346 (holotype) H-K 3344 A, B vulva dorsal view C, D vulva ventral view E palp prolateral view F palp ventral view G palp retrolateral view H-K palp distal view. Scale bar: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.888.34494.figure11" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/354502" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" tableDoi="10.3897/zookeys.888.34494.figure11">Fig. 11I, J</figureCitation>
). Females of 
<taxonomicName genus="H." lsidName="H. kojima" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="kojima">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">H. kojima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov. resemble those of other Amami group 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Liphistiidae" genus="Heptathela" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Heptathela" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Heptathela</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species but differ from those of other Amami group 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Liphistiidae" genus="Heptathela" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Heptathela" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Heptathela</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species by paired receptacular clusters close to each other (
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 11" captionStartId="F11" captionText="Figure 11. Male and female genital anatomy of Heptathela kojima sp. nov. A, C 3339 (short for XUX- 2013 - 339) B, D 3340 E-G 3346 (holotype) H-K 3344 A, B vulva dorsal view C, D vulva ventral view E palp prolateral view F palp ventral view G palp retrolateral view H-K palp distal view. Scale bar: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.888.34494.figure11" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/354502" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" tableDoi="10.3897/zookeys.888.34494.figure11">Fig. 11B, D</figureCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName genus="H." lsidName="H. kojima" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="kojima">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">H. kojima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov. can also be diagnosed from all other Amami group 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Liphistiidae" genus="Heptathela" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Heptathela" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Heptathela</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species by the following unique nucleotide substitutions in the standard DNA barcode alignment: C (44), C (56), C (128), A (131), C (134), C (137), C (155), G (158), G (176), T (230), T (245), C (269), T (320), C (357), C (377), A (378), A (443), C (446), G (464), A (479), C (518), G (521), T (554), A (560), C (608), C (611).
</paragraph>
