<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Male</emphasis>
(Holotype). Carapace brown; opisthosoma light brown, with dark brown tergites close to each other; cheliceral groove with eleven denticles; seven spinnerets. Measurements: BL 7.30, CL 3.60, CW 3.30, OL 3.60, OW 2.70; ALE&gt; PLE&gt; PME&gt; AME; leg I 14.90 (4.20 + 165 + 3.15 + 4.00 + 1.90), leg II 16.10 (4.20 + 1.85 + 3.25 + 4.40 + 2.40), leg III 16.85 (4.25 + 1.90 + 3.20 + 5.00 + 2.50), leg IV 21.70 (5.50 + 2.00 + 4.20 + 6.90 + 3.10).
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Palp</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Prolateral side of paracymbium unpigmented and unsclerotised, numerous setae and spines at the tip of paracymbium (
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 11" captionStartId="F11" captionText="Figure 11. Male and female genital anatomy of Heptathela kojima sp. nov. A, C 3339 (short for XUX- 2013 - 339) B, D 3340 E-G 3346 (holotype) H-K 3344 A, B vulva dorsal view C, D vulva ventral view E palp prolateral view F palp ventral view G palp retrolateral view H-K palp distal view. Scale bar: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.888.34494.figure11" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/354502" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" tableDoi="10.3897/zookeys.888.34494.figure11">
Fig. 11
<normalizedToken originalValue="E–G">E-G</normalizedToken>
</figureCitation>
). Contrategulum with serrated margin (
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 11" captionStartId="F11" captionText="Figure 11. Male and female genital anatomy of Heptathela kojima sp. nov. A, C 3339 (short for XUX- 2013 - 339) B, D 3340 E-G 3346 (holotype) H-K 3344 A, B vulva dorsal view C, D vulva ventral view E palp prolateral view F palp ventral view G palp retrolateral view H-K palp distal view. Scale bar: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.888.34494.figure11" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/354502" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" tableDoi="10.3897/zookeys.888.34494.figure11">Fig. 11E, H, I</figureCitation>
). Conductor base wide, leaf-shaped and rugose, with several folds and gradually narrowing to a short spiniform apex (
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 11" captionStartId="F11" captionText="Figure 11. Male and female genital anatomy of Heptathela kojima sp. nov. A, C 3339 (short for XUX- 2013 - 339) B, D 3340 E-G 3346 (holotype) H-K 3344 A, B vulva dorsal view C, D vulva ventral view E palp prolateral view F palp ventral view G palp retrolateral view H-K palp distal view. Scale bar: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.888.34494.figure11" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/354502" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" tableDoi="10.3897/zookeys.888.34494.figure11">Fig. 11I, J</figureCitation>
). Embolus sclerotised, with a wide and flat opening (
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 11" captionStartId="F11" captionText="Figure 11. Male and female genital anatomy of Heptathela kojima sp. nov. A, C 3339 (short for XUX- 2013 - 339) B, D 3340 E-G 3346 (holotype) H-K 3344 A, B vulva dorsal view C, D vulva ventral view E palp prolateral view F palp ventral view G palp retrolateral view H-K palp distal view. Scale bar: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.888.34494.figure11" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/354502" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" tableDoi="10.3897/zookeys.888.34494.figure11">
Fig. 11
<normalizedToken originalValue="H–K">H-K</normalizedToken>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Females</emphasis>
(
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">N</emphasis>
= 6). Carapace and opisthosoma colour as in male; cheliceral groove with 13 pronounced denticles; tergites similar to male; 6-8 spinnerets. Measurements: BL 9.00-11.50, CL 4.90-6.15, CW 4.25-5.20, OL 4.30-6.10, OW 3.00-4.50; ALE&gt; PLE&gt; PME&gt; AME; palp 9.05 (3.25 + 1.65 + 1.85 + 2.30), leg I 10.50 (3.35 + 1.80 + 2.00 + 2.10 + 1.25), leg II 10.05 (3.10 + 1.80 + 1.75 + 2.10 + 1.30), leg III 10.45 (2.90 + 1.95 + 1.65 + 2.40 + 1.55), leg IV 15.20 (4.40 + 2.20 + 2.60 + 4.00 + 2.00).
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Female genitalia</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
A pair of indistinct depressions on the ventro-lateral part of genital atrium (
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 11" captionStartId="F11" captionText="Figure 11. Male and female genital anatomy of Heptathela kojima sp. nov. A, C 3339 (short for XUX- 2013 - 339) B, D 3340 E-G 3346 (holotype) H-K 3344 A, B vulva dorsal view C, D vulva ventral view E palp prolateral view F palp ventral view G palp retrolateral view H-K palp distal view. Scale bar: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.888.34494.figure11" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/354502" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" tableDoi="10.3897/zookeys.888.34494.figure11">Fig. 11C, D</figureCitation>
). Paired receptacular clusters separated from each other along the anterior margin of bursa copulatrix, or fused together, divided into two parts, without genital stalks (
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 11" captionStartId="F11" captionText="Figure 11. Male and female genital anatomy of Heptathela kojima sp. nov. A, C 3339 (short for XUX- 2013 - 339) B, D 3340 E-G 3346 (holotype) H-K 3344 A, B vulva dorsal view C, D vulva ventral view E palp prolateral view F palp ventral view G palp retrolateral view H-K palp distal view. Scale bar: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.888.34494.figure11" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/354502" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" tableDoi="10.3897/zookeys.888.34494.figure11">
Fig. 11
<normalizedToken originalValue="A–D">A-D</normalizedToken>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="etymology">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">The species epithet, a noun in apposition, refers to the type locality.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
The species is endemic to the Japanese island Tokunoshima (
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. General somatic morphology of Heptathela kimurai (Kishida, 1920) A dorsal view B ventral view and map showing the sampling localities of Heptathela specimens from Kyushu to central Ryukyus (C)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.888.34494.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/354492" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" tableDoi="10.3897/zookeys.888.34494.figure1">Fig. 1C</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
